12/04/220  This is the source I am running pqpf cron jobs

this directory is cheked out from GitHub: DingchenHou-NOAA, hotfix/pqpf branch
 
to set up a cron job, please do the following:

cd pqpf
modify set_pqpf_cron.sh for WORK_DIR and CHECK_DIR
modify user_full.conf for SDATE and EDATE
run et_pqpf_cron.sh
cd $WORK_DIR
cd rocoto
compile_install_all.sh -b yes   (set up the cfron)

When you need to rest SDATE/EDATE
modify user_full.conf
compile_install_all.sh -r yes

If a cycle is not run (due to e.g. missing gefs prod files), you
need to copy the  folllowing files from the prod machine
enspost_grb2.tXXz.frzr
enspost_grb2.tXXz.icep
enspost_grb2.tXXz.prcp
enspost_grb2.tXXz.snow
enspost_grb2.tXXz.rain
to the $COMOUT directory 
and then modify the rocoto/bin/*p35/enspost.hr file in $WORK_DIR with
COMIN=/gpfs/dell6/ptmp/Dingchen.Hou/o/ThHa/com/gefs/dev/gefs.20201207/06
(check your $COMOUT path to make sure $COMIN matches with it) 
